ntroller {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    /// Caches peers whose routing key didn't match any contact at discovery time.\n    /// Keyed by mDNS instance name (consistent with `peer_index`).\n    stranger_cache: HashMap<String, RawDiscoveredPeer>,\n}\n```\n\nIn `new()` (line 200), add to the `Self` construction:\n\n```rust\nstranger_cache: HashMap::new(),\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client --lib discovery::controller::tests::stranger_is_cached_on_discovery`\nExpected: PASS\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Write failing test — handle_discovered caches stranger**\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn handle_discovered_caches_stranger() {\n    let identity = Identity::generate();\n    let pubkey = *identity.public_id();\n    let rk: [u8; 16] = *pubkey.routing_key();\n\n    // Controller has NO contacts — all peers are strangers.\n    let mut controller = DiscoveryController::new(vec![], 256, test_registry()).unwrap();\n    let coordinator = TransportCoordinator::new(CoordinatorConfig::default());\n\n    let peer = RawDiscoveredPeer {\n        instance_name: \"stranger-peer\".to_string(),\n        addresses: vec![\"192.168.1.50\".parse().unwrap()],\n        port: 23003,\n        txt_records: reme_discovery::encode_txt(&rk, 23003),\n        discovered_at: Instant::now(),\n    };\n\n    controller.handle_discovered(peer, &coordinator).await;\n\n    assert_eq!(controller.stranger_cache.len(), 1);\n    assert!(controller.stranger_cache.contains_key(\"stranger-peer\"));\n    // Not in peer_index — strangers aren't verified.\n    assert!(controller.peer_index.is_empty());\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client --lib discovery::controller::tests::handle_discovered_caches_stranger`\nExpected: FAIL — stranger is discarded, cache stays empty.\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Modify handle_discovered to cache strangers**\n\nIn `handle_discovered()`, replace the early return at lines 290-296:\n\n```rust\nlet Some(candidates) = self.contact_index.get(&routing_key) else {\n    debug!(\n        instance = %peer.instance_name,\n        \"Ignoring stranger (routing key not in contacts)\"\n    );\n    return;\n};\n```\n\nWith:\n\n```rust\nlet Some(candidates) = self.contact_index.get(&routing_key) else {\n    if self.stranger_cache.len() < self.max_peers {\n        debug!(\n            instance = %peer.instance_name,\n            \"Caching stranger (routing key not in contacts)\"\n        );\n        self.stranger_cache.insert(peer.instance_name.clone(), peer);\n    } else {\n        debug!(\n            instance = %peer.instance_name,\n            max = self.max_peers,\n            \"Stranger cache full, dropping peer\"\n        );\n    }\n    return;\n};\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client --lib discovery::controller::tests::handle_discovered_caches_stranger`\nExpected: PASS\n\n- [ ] **Step 9: Run full test suite**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client`\nExpected: All tests pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 10: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(discovery): cache unknown mDNS peers as strangers\n\nWhen a discovered peer's routing key doesn't match any contact,\nstore it in stranger_cache instead of discarding. This prepares\nfor re-processing when a matching contact is added later.\n\nPart of #100.\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Clean stranger cache on PeerLost\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs:547-549` (`handle_lost()`)\n- Test: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs` (inline `mod tests`)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write failing test**\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn peer_lost_cleans_stranger_cache() {\n    let mut controller = DiscoveryController::new(vec![], 256, test_registry()).unwrap();\n    let coordinator = TransportCoordinator::new(CoordinatorConfig::default());\n\n    let rk = [0xAAu8; 16];\n    let peer = RawDiscoveredPeer {\n        instance_name: \"will-be-lost\".to_string(),\n        addresses: vec![\"192.168.1.50\".parse().unwrap()],\n        port: 23003,\n        txt_records: reme_discovery::encode_txt(&rk, 23003),\n        discovered_at: Instant::now(),\n    };\n\n    controller.handle_discovered(peer, &coordinator).await;\n    assert_eq!(controller.stranger_cache.len(), 1);\n\n    controller.handle_lost(\"will-be-lost\", &coordinator);\n    assert!(controller.stranger_cache.is_empty());\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client --lib discovery::controller::tests::peer_lost_cleans_stranger_cache`\nExpected: FAIL — `handle_lost` doesn't touch `stranger_cache`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add stranger cache cleanup to handle_lost**\n\nIn `handle_lost()` (line 547), add cleanup before or after the existing `remove_peer` call:\n\n```rust\nfn handle_lost(&mut self, instance_name: &str, coordinator: &TransportCoordinator) {\n    self.stranger_cache.remove(instance_name);\n    self.remove_peer(instance_name, coordinator);\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client --lib discovery::controller::tests::peer_lost_cleans_stranger_cache`\nExpected: PASS\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(discovery): clean stranger cache on PeerLost\n\nRemove peers from the stranger cache when they leave the network,\npreventing stale entries from accumulating.\n\nPart of #100.\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Re-process cached strangers when a new contact is added\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs:151-160` (`contact_rx` arm in `spawn()`)\n- Add method: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs` (`drain_matching_strangers()`)\n- Test: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs` (inline `mod tests`)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write failing test — cached stranger is re-processed on contact add**\n\nThis test verifies the full flow: discover stranger → add contact → stranger gets processed. Since `handle_discovered` does HTTP identity verification (which we can't easily mock), we test `drain_matching_strangers()` separately and verify the stranger is removed from cache and returned.\n\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn drain_matching_strangers_returns_matches() {\n    let mut controller = DiscoveryController::new(vec![], 256, test_registry()).unwrap();\n\n    let rk = [0xBBu8; 16];\n    let peer = RawDiscoveredPeer {\n        instance_name: \"cached-stranger\".to_string(),\n        addresses: vec![\"192.168.1.50\".parse().unwrap()],\n        port: 23003,\n        txt_records: reme_discovery::encode_txt(&rk, 23003),\n        discovered_at: Instant::now(),\n    };\n    controller\n        .stranger_cache\n        .insert(peer.instance_name.clone(), peer);\n    assert_eq!(controller.stranger_cache.len(), 1);\n\n    let matches = controller.drain_matching_strangers(&rk);\n    assert_eq!(matches.len(), 1);\n    assert_eq!(matches[0].instance_name, \"cached-stranger\");\n    assert!(controller.stranger_cache.is_empty());\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client --lib discovery::controller::tests::drain_matching_strangers_returns_matches`\nExpected: FAIL — method doesn't exist.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement drain_matching_strangers**\n\nAdd method to `DiscoveryController`:\n\n```rust\n/// Remove and return all cached strangers whose routing key matches `target_rk`.\nfn drain_matching_strangers(&mut self, target_rk: &[u8; 16]) -> Vec<RawDiscoveredPeer> {\n    let matching_keys: Vec<String> = self\n        .stranger_cache\n        .iter()\n        .filter_map(|(name, peer)| {\n            match decode_txt(&peer.txt_records) {\n                Ok(fields) if fields.routing_key == *target_rk => Some(name.clone()),\n                _ => None,\n            }\n        })\n        .collect();\n\n    matching_keys\n        .into_iter()\n        .filter_map(|name| self.stranger_cache.remove(&name))\n        .collect()\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client --lib discovery::controller::tests::drain_matching_strangers_returns_matches`\nExpected: PASS\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Write test — non-matching strangers are not drained**\n\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn drain_matching_strangers_ignores_non_matches() {\n    let mut controller = DiscoveryController::new(vec![], 256, test_registry()).unwrap();\n\n    let rk_a = [0xAAu8; 16];\n    let rk_b = [0xBBu8; 16];\n\n    let peer = RawDiscoveredPeer {\n        instance_name: \"other-stranger\".to_string(),\n        addresses: vec![\"192.168.1.50\".parse().unwrap()],\n        port: 23003,\n        txt_records: reme_discovery::encode_txt(&rk_a, 23003),\n        discovered_at: Instant::now(),\n    };\n    controller\n        .stranger_cache\n        .insert(peer.instance_name.clone(), peer);\n\n    let matches = controller.drain_matching_strangers(&rk_b);\n    assert!(matches.is_empty());\n    assert_eq!(controller.stranger_cache.len(), 1);\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Run test to verify it passes immediately**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client --lib discovery::controller::tests::drain_matching_strangers_ignores_non_matches`\nExpected: PASS (the implementation already handles this).\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Wire drain_matching_strangers into the contact_rx arm**\n\nIn the `spawn()` function, update the `contact_rx` arm (lines 151-160):\n\n```rust\nSome((pubkey, routing_key)) = contact_rx.recv() => {\n    let candidates = controller.contact_index.entry(routing_key).or_default();\n    if !candidates.contains(&pubkey) {\n        candidates.push(pubkey);\n    }\n    debug!(\n        pubkey = %hex::encode(pubkey.to_bytes()),\n        \"Added new contact to discovery controller\"\n    );\n\n    // Re-process any cached strangers whose routing key matches\n    // the newly added contact.\n    let cached_peers = controller.drain_matching_strangers(&routing_key);\n    for peer in cached_peers {\n        debug!(\n            instance = %peer.instance_name,\n            \"Re-processing cached stranger for new contact\"\n        );\n        controller.handle_discovered(peer, &coordinator).await;\n        peer_count.store(controller.peer_index.len(), Ordering::Relaxed);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Run full test suite**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client`\nExpected: All tests pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 9: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(discovery): re-process cached strangers on new contact\n\nWhen a new contact is added, scan the stranger cache for peers whose\nrouting key matches. Matching peers are removed from the cache and\nfed through handle_discovered() for identity verification and\ntransport registration.\n\nCloses #100.\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Stranger cache cap enforcement\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs` (test only — capping logic already in Task 1)\n- Test: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs` (inline `mod tests`)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write test — cache respects max_peers cap**\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn stranger_cache_respects_max_peers() {\n    // max_peers = 2 (clamped from 2, above the min of 1)\n    let mut controller = DiscoveryController::new(vec![], 2, test_registry()).unwrap();\n    let coordinator = TransportCoordinator::new(CoordinatorConfig::default());\n\n    for i in 0..3 {\n        let mut rk = [0u8; 16];\n        rk[0] = i;\n        let peer = RawDiscoveredPeer {\n            instance_name: format!(\"stranger-{i}\"),\n            addresses: vec![\"192.168.1.50\".parse().unwrap()],\n            port: 23003,\n            txt_records: reme_discovery::encode_txt(&rk, 23003),\n            discovered_at: Instant::now(),\n        };\n        controller.handle_discovered(peer, &coordinator).await;\n    }\n\n    // Only 2 should be cached (max_peers = 2), third is dropped.\n    assert_eq!(controller.stranger_cache.len(), 2);\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client --lib discovery::controller::tests::stranger_cache_respects_max_peers`\nExpected: PASS (capping logic was added in Task 1 Step 7).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run full workspace checks**\n\nRun: `cargo fmt --all -- --check && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings && cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`\nExpected: All pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit (if any fixes needed from step 3)**\n\nOnly if clippy/fmt required changes.\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Shutdown cleanup\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs:168-176` (shutdown block in `spawn()`)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Clear stranger cache on shutdown**\n\nIn the shutdown block (line 168), add `stranger_cache` cleanup alongside existing `peer_index` drain:\n\n```rust\n// Deregister all tracked peers on shutdown.\nfor (name, entry) in controller.peer_index.drain() {\n    let target_id = TargetId::http(&entry.url);\n    coordinator.remove_http_target(&target_id);\n    controller.registry.remove_meta(&target_id);\n    debug!(instance = %name, \"Deregistered peer on shutdown\");\n}\ncontroller.verified_peer_index.clear();\ncontroller.stranger_cache.clear();\npeer_count.store(0, Ordering::Relaxed);\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run full workspace checks**\n\nRun: `cargo fmt --all -- --check && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings && cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`\nExpected: All pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs\ngit commit -m \"chore(discovery): clear stranger cache on controller shutdown\n\nPart of #100.\"\n```\n",
