            "content": "# Parallel Peer Refresh — Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Replace sequential peer verification in `refresh_all_peers` with concurrent verification using `JoinSet`, reducing worst-case refresh time from ~21 minutes to ~5 seconds.\n\n**Architecture:** Extract the HTTP identity verification logic into a standalone `async fn` that owns all its data. Replace the sequential loop with `JoinSet::spawn` per peer. Collect results and apply success/failure mutations to `peer_index` sequentially after all tasks complete.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Rust, tokio (`JoinSet`), reqwest (clone-cheap `Client`)\n\n**Spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-27-parallel-peer-refresh.md`\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Extract standalone verify function\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs:624-689` (`verify_peer_identity` + new standalone fn)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add the standalone async function**\n\nAdd this function **above** the `impl DiscoveryController` block (it's a module-level free function, not a method):\n\n```rust\n/// Perform identity challenge-response verification against a single peer.\n///\n/// Standalone version that owns all data, suitable for use in spawned tasks.\n// FIXME(SEC-3): channel binding not implemented — responder IP:port not in signed data\nasync fn verify_identity(\n    http_client: reqwest::Client,\n    base_url: String,\n    candidates: Vec<PublicID>,\n) -> Result<Option<PublicID>, reqwest::Error> {\n    let challenge: [u8; 32] = rand::random();\n    let challenge_b64 = BASE64_STANDARD.encode(challenge);\n    let challenge_encoded = percent_encode(challenge_b64.as_bytes(), NON_ALPHANUMERIC);\n\n    let url = format!(\n        \"{}/api/v1/identity?challenge={}\",\n        base_url.trim_end_matches('/'),\n        challenge_encoded\n    );\n\n    let mut resp = http_client.get(&url).send().await?;\n\n    if !resp.status().is_success() {\n        debug!(status = %resp.status(), \"Identity challenge returned non-success\");\n        return Ok(None);\n    }\n\n    #[allow(clippy::cast_possible_truncation)]\n    let max = MAX_IDENTITY_RESPONSE_BYTES as usize;\n    let mut buf = Vec::with_capacity(max);\n    while let Some(chunk) = resp.chunk().await? {\n        if buf.len() + chunk.len() > max {\n            debug!(\n                size = buf.len() + chunk.len(),\n                \"Identity response too large, skipping\"\n            );\n            return Ok(None);\n        }\n        buf.extend_from_slice(&chunk);\n    }\n    let Ok(body) = serde_json::from_slice::<IdentityResponse>(&buf) else {\n        debug!(\"Failed to parse identity response\");\n        return Ok(None);\n    };\n\n    let Ok(sig_bytes) = BASE64_STANDARD.decode(&body.signature) else {\n        debug!(\"Failed to base64-decode identity signature\");\n        return Ok(None);\n    };\n    let Ok(signature): Result<[u8; 64], _> = sig_bytes.try_into() else {\n        debug!(\"Identity signature has wrong length (expected 64 bytes)\");\n        return Ok(None);\n    };\n\n    let mut matched: Option<PublicID> = None;\n    for candidate in &candidates {\n        let sign_data = build_identity_sign_data(&challenge, &candidate.to_bytes());\n        if candidate.verify_xeddsa(&sign_data, &signature) && matched.is_none() {\n            matched = Some(*candidate);\n        }\n    }\n\n    Ok(matched)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Rewrite `verify_peer_identity` as a thin wrapper**\n\nReplace the existing `verify_peer_identity` method body on `DiscoveryController` with:\n\n```rust\n    // FIXME(SEC-3): channel binding not implemented — responder IP:port not in signed data\n    async fn verify_peer_identity(\n        &self,\n        base_url: &str,\n        candidates: &[PublicID],\n    ) -> Result<Option<PublicID>, reqwest::Error> {\n        verify_identity(\n            self.http_client.clone(),\n            base_url.to_owned(),\n            candidates.to_vec(),\n        )\n        .await\n    }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run tests to verify no behavior change**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client -- discovery::controller::tests`\nExpected: All 15 tests pass (pure refactor, identical behavior).\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run clippy**\n\nRun: `cargo clippy -p client -- -D warnings`\nExpected: Clean.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs\ngit commit -m \"refactor(discovery): extract standalone verify_identity function\n\nExtract the HTTP identity verification logic into a free async function\nthat owns all its data. The existing verify_peer_identity method becomes\na thin wrapper. This prepares for concurrent verification in JoinSet.\n\nPart of #101.\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Parallelize refresh_all_peers with JoinSet\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs:1` (add `JoinSet` import)\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs:237-288` (`refresh_all_peers`)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add JoinSet import**\n\nUpdate the tokio import line:\n\n```rust\nuse tokio::task::{JoinHandle, JoinSet};\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Rewrite refresh_all_peers**\n\nReplace the entire `refresh_all_peers` method body:\n\n```rust\n    /// Periodic refresh: re-verify every tracked peer concurrently using\n    /// [`JoinSet`]. On failure, increment the failure counter; at\n    /// [`FAILURE_THRESHOLD`] consecutive failures, remove the peer entirely\n    /// (ephemeral circuit breaker). On success, reset the counter.\n    async fn refresh_all_peers(&mut self, coordinator: &TransportCoordinator) {\n        let peers: Vec<(String, String, PublicID)> = self\n            .peer_index\n            .iter()\n            .map(|(name, entry)| (name.clone(), entry.url.clone(), entry.verified_identity))\n            .collect();\n\n        if peers.is_empty() {\n            return;\n        }\n\n        debug!(count = peers.len(), \"Starting periodic peer refresh\");\n\n        let mut set = JoinSet::new();\n        for (name, url, identity) in peers {\n            let client = self.http_client.clone();\n            set.spawn(async move {\n                let result = verify_identity(client, url, vec![identity]).await;\n                (name, result)\n            });\n        }\n\n        let mut to_remove = Vec::new();\n\n        while let Some(res) = set.join_next().await {\n            match res {\n                Ok((name, Ok(Some(_)))) => {\n                    if let Some(entry) = self.peer_index.get_mut(&name) {\n                        if entry.failure_count > 0 {\n                            debug!(instance = %name, \"Peer refresh succeeded, resetting failure count\");\n                        }\n                        entry.failure_count = 0;\n                    }\n                }\n                Ok((name, Ok(None) | Err(_))) => {\n                    if let Some(entry) = self.peer_index.get_mut(&name) {\n                        entry.failure_count += 1;\n                        debug!(\n                            instance = %name,\n                            failures = entry.failure_count,\n                            \"Peer refresh verification failed\"\n                        );\n                        if entry.failure_count >= FAILURE_THRESHOLD {\n                            to_remove.push(name);\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n                Err(e) => {\n                    warn!(\"Peer refresh task panicked: {e}\");\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        for name in to_remove {\n            info!(\n                instance = %name,\n                \"Removing stale peer after {} consecutive verification failures\",\n                FAILURE_THRESHOLD\n            );\n            self.remove_peer(&name, coordinator);\n        }\n    }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run tests**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client -- discovery::controller::tests`\nExpected: All 15 tests pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run full workspace checks**\n\nRun: `cargo fmt --all -- --check && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings && cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`\nExpected: All pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(discovery): parallelize periodic peer refresh with JoinSet\n\nReplace sequential peer re-verification loop with concurrent JoinSet.\nEach verification runs as an independent task sharing the reqwest\nconnection pool. Results are collected and applied sequentially.\n\nWith max_peers=256 and 5s timeout, worst-case refresh drops from\n~21 minutes (sequential) to ~5 seconds (concurrent).\n\nCloses #101.\"\n```\n",
